Polyfloral honey is considered by most specialists to be a complete honey, used in the treatment of many diseases and ailments. The composition includes vitamins from the B and C complex, enzymes, organic acids (lactic acid, gluconic acid) and various mineral salts (iron, phosphorus, calcium, potassium). It is easy to assimilate due to its content of glucose, sucrose and fructose.      Polyfloral honey has an energy value of 3000 kcal per 1 kilogram. Even if it is crystallized, its healing properties are not lost. Specialists recommend that honey be consumed in moderation, two or three teaspoons mixed with milk or fruit, two or three times a day. This type of honey is recommended for the treatment of anorexia, due to its high iron content. Polyfloral honey stimulates the appetite, facilitates the digestive process, improves the activity of the heart and liver and causes an increase in the percentage of hemoglobin in the blood. It is also an excellent remedy for physical and mental fatigue. Regular consumption prevents problems with bone growth and demineralization.
